The House Committee on Public Safety and Homeland Security offers the following
substitute to HB 138:
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Code Section 35-8-7 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to the
2 powers and duties of the Georgia Peace Officer Standards and Training Council, so as
3 establish basic and in-service training courses on de-escalation techniques and methods; to
4 provide for an effective date; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and
5 for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Code Section 35-8-7 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to the powers and
9 duties of the Georgia Peace Officer Standards and Training Council, is amended by revising
10 paragraph (20) as follows:
11 "(20) To establish as part of the curriculum for basic and in-service training courses for
12 all peace officers training on organized criminal activity, and criminal street gangs, and
13 de-escalation techniques and methods that include scenario based training;"
14 SECTION 2.
15 This Act shall become effective on January 1, 2026.
